	<h2><TMPL_VAR NAME="PAGE_TITLE"> Tips</h2>
	<p><strong>Death Record results vary by state, but may include: Decedent Name, SSN, Address, County of Residence, Date of Birth, Date of Death, Social Security Administration Verified or Proof indicator, Location of Death, and Death Certificate Number.</strong></p>

	<p>&nbsp;</p>
        <p>Find a Death Record by using one or more of the following search techniques:</p>
        <p>&nbsp;</p>

	<ol id="font81">
	  <li>Search by Name and State. If too many records are returned, try adding a City. You can also use a partial first name.<br />
          <br /></li>
	  <li>Search by Name and Date of Birth. If too many records are returned, try adding a City and State. You can also use a partial first name.<br />
	  <br /></li>
	  <li>Search by Name and Date of Death. If too many records are returned, try adding a City and State. You can also use a partial first name.<br />
	  <br /></li>
	  <li>Search by Social Security Number.<br />
	  </li>
	  </ol>
	<p>&nbsp;</p>
        <p>Some records may have supplemental information which can be obtained by clicking on the Death Record Report icon and purchasing the Death Record Report.</p>
	<p>&nbsp;</p>

